## Practical Usage Examples

### 1. Multi-Client Presentation

**Base template**: `client-presentation-template.slidelang`

```yaml
---
mode: flex
title: "Proposal for {{client_name}}"
variables:
  # Client-specific variables
  client_name: "TechCorp Global"
  client_industry: "Technology"
  client_size: "2,500 employees"
  client_challenge: "Fragmented content management"

  # Proposal variables
  proposed_solution: "ContentOS Enterprise"
  implementation_time: "6 weeks"
  expected_roi: "340%"

  # Team variables
  account_manager: "María González"
  technical_lead: "Carlos Rodríguez"
---

# Custom Proposal for {{client_name}}
## Transforming content management in {{client_industry}}

Dear **{{client_name}}** team,

We've designed a solution specifically for companies of {{client_size}} in the {{client_industry}} sector facing the challenge of {{client_challenge}}.

### Our Proposal: {{proposed_solution}}

- **Implementation time**: {{implementation_time}}
- **Expected ROI**: {{expected_roi}}
- **Account Manager**: {{account_manager}}
- **Technical Lead**: {{technical_lead}}
```

### 2. Automated Monthly Reports

**Template**: `monthly-report-template.slidelang`

```yaml
---
mode: flex
title: "Monthly Report {{month}} {{year}}"
variables:
  # Report period
  month: "January"
  year: "2025"
  quarter: "Q1"

  # Key metrics
  revenue: "$487K"
  growth: "+12.3%"
  new_customers: "247"
  churn_rate: "2.1%"

  # Responsible team
  analyst: "{{author_name}}"
  reviewer: "Director of Analytics"
  approval_date: "{{last_updated}}"
---

# Performance Report {{month}} {{year}}
## Complete business metrics analysis

**Analyst**: {{analyst}}
**Reviewer**: {{reviewer}}
**Approval date**: {{approval_date}}

### Executive Summary {{quarter}}

- **Revenue**: {{revenue}} ({{growth}} vs previous month)
- **New customers**: {{new_customers}}
- **Churn rate**: {{churn_rate}}
```

### 3. Versioned Product Documentation

```yaml
---
mode: flex
title: "{{product_name}} - Documentation {{guide_version}}"
variables:
  # Product information
  product_name: "DataFlow API"
  guide_version: "v2.1"
  api_version: "2.1.3"

  # Dynamic URLs
  base_url: "https://api.dataflow.com/v2"
  docs_url: "https://docs.dataflow.com/{{api_version}}"
  github_url: "https://github.com/dataflow/api/tree/v{{api_version}}"

  # Technical information
  rate_limit: "1000 requests/hour"
  response_format: "JSON"
  auth_method: "Bearer Token"
---

# {{product_name}} - Developer Guide
## Version {{guide_version}} | API {{api_version}}

### Base Configuration

```javascript
const apiClient = new DataFlowAPI({
  baseURL: '{{base_url}}',
  version: '{{api_version}}',
  auth: '{{auth_method}}'
});
```

### Limits and Restrictions

- **Rate limiting**: {{rate_limit}}
- **Response format**: {{response_format}}
- **Authentication**: {{auth_method}}

### Additional Resources

- 📚 **Complete documentation**: [{{docs_url}}]({{docs_url}})
- 🐙 **Source code**: [{{github_url}}]({{github_url}})
```

