## Best Practices for Variables

### 1. **Consistent Naming**

```yaml
# ✅ Good: consistent snake_case
variables:
  product_name: "My Product"
  release_date: "2025-01-15"
  target_audience: "developers"

# ❌ Bad: Mixed styles
variables:
  productName: "My Product"       # camelCase
  release-date: "2025-01-15"      # kebab-case
  target_audience: "developers"   # snake_case
```

### 2. **Logical Grouping**

```yaml
variables:
  # Product information
  product:
    name: "SlideLang Pro"
    version: "v3.1"
    category: "Productivity"

  # Business metrics
  metrics:
    users: "15,847"
    revenue: "$487K"
    growth: "+28.5%"

  # Contact information
  contact:
    sales: "sales@company.com"
    support: "+1 (555) 123-4567"
```

### 3. **Inline Documentation**

```yaml
variables:
  # Prices in USD (update quarterly)
  pricing_basic: "$29"          # Individual plan
  pricing_pro: "$79"            # Plan for small teams
  pricing_enterprise: "Custom"  # Corporate plan

  # Q1 2025 metrics (source: Analytics Dashboard)
  conversion_rate: "4.2%"       # Lead to customer
  churn_rate: "1.8%"           # Monthly churn
  nps_score: "73"              # Net Promoter Score
```

### 4. **Variable Validation**

```yaml
# Variables with default values
variables:
  environment: "{{ENV | default('production')}}"
  debug_mode: "{{DEBUG | default(false)}}"
  max_users: "{{MAX_USERS | default(1000)}}"

  # Required variables (will fail if not defined)
  api_key: "{{REQUIRED_API_KEY}}"
  client_id: "{{REQUIRED_CLIENT_ID}}"
```

